<paragraph id="IAS19_BC266" base="F16152501" principles="no"><paranum>BC266</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 19"/><data name="paranum" value="BC266"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS19_P1673" outputclass="keep_with_next">To avoid an inconsistency in the timing of       recognition for related transactions, the Board decided that:</p><ol id="IAS19_L0205" base="F16152512" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p id="IAS19_P1674" base="F16152513" outputclass="keep_with_next">past service cost should           be recognised at the earlier of:</p>         <ol id="IAS19_L0206" base="F16152515" type="lower-roman"><li><li_value>(i)</li_value>             <p id="IAS19_P1675" base="F16152516">when the plan amendment occurs; and</p></li><li><li_value>(ii)</li_value>             <p id="IAS19_P1676" base="F16152518">when any related restructuring costs or termination               benefits are recognised.</p></li></ol></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p id="IAS19_P1677" base="F16152520" outputclass="keep_with_next">termination benefits           should be recognised at the earlier of:</p>         <ol id="IAS19_L0207" base="F16152522" type="lower-roman"><li><li_value>(i)</li_value>             <p id="IAS19_P1678" base="F16152523">when the entity can no longer withdraw the offer of               those benefits; and</p></li><li><li_value>(ii)</li_value>             <p id="IAS19_P1679" base="F16152525">when any related restructuring costs are               recognised.</p></li></ol></li></ol></body></paragraph>